WEBVTT

00:00:04.839 --> 00:00:10.177
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:11.053 --> 00:00:14.140
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:15.057 --> 00:00:16.726
At least it is true...

00:00:17.226 --> 00:00:21.022
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:28.988 --> 00:00:30.906
I told you this long ago...

00:00:31.407 --> 00:00:33.451
You are mine.

00:00:34.201 --> 00:00:36.954
If you want to get free of my hand...

00:00:37.163 --> 00:00:38.581
...by those conditions...

00:00:39.081 --> 00:00:40.958
Snatch yourself free with your blade!

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:48.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:01:29.840 --> 00:01:30.674
Bye...

00:02:00.871 --> 00:02:02.873
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:02:03.082 --> 00:02:04.875
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:08.546
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:02:08.796 --> 00:02:10.923
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:02:11.132 --> 00:02:13.050
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:02:13.175 --> 00:02:15.261
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:02:15.427 --> 00:02:17.054
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:02:17.304 --> 00:02:20.683
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:02:21.433 --> 00:02:24.311
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:02:25.146 --> 00:02:25.771
<i>I...</i>

00:02:26.147 --> 00:02:26.814
<i>... can...</i>

00:02:26.939 --> 00:02:29.024
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:02:29.191 --> 00:02:30.067
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:30.276 --> 00:02:31.026
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:31.193 --> 00:02:32.820
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:02:33.070 --> 00:02:34.029
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:34.196 --> 00:02:34.947
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:35.156 --> 00:02:36.949
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:02:37.199 --> 00:02:38.075
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:38.284 --> 00:02:39.076
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:39.326 --> 00:02:40.828
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:02:40.828 --> 00:02:41.829
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:42.079 --> 00:02:42.955
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:43.789
<i>Too late...</i>

00:02:43.914 --> 00:02:45.416
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:02:50.671 --> 00:02:54.675
Sparks

00:03:19.116 --> 00:03:21.202
They look brave enough.

00:03:21.368 --> 00:03:26.081
So many plucky fellows have
gathered to fight in my tournament!

00:03:26.332 --> 00:03:30.002
My Lord, the final match
will begin at any moment.

00:03:33.380 --> 00:03:37.384
He is a mercenary called Valencia,
well known as the Prince of Massacre.

00:03:37.509 --> 00:03:39.511
It's been said that he slaughtered...

00:03:39.720 --> 00:03:44.642
...over one hundred and thirty of
Midland's soldiers during the hundred-year war.

00:03:53.108 --> 00:03:57.488
I am quite sure that Valencia will win...

00:04:09.041 --> 00:04:10.042
Who is he?

00:04:10.376 --> 00:04:11.919
Hey, what are you doing?

00:04:13.629 --> 00:04:14.922
Can't you tell?

00:04:15.047 --> 00:04:15.923
I'm a challenger.

00:04:16.048 --> 00:04:17.132
That's ridiculous!

00:04:17.258 --> 00:04:18.968
I am taking him on...

00:04:22.137 --> 00:04:24.139
Take it easy, big guy.

00:04:24.265 --> 00:04:25.641
This tournament is for everyone.

00:04:27.726 --> 00:04:30.145
You look very skilled.

00:04:30.604 --> 00:04:33.649
So, won't you play with me now?

00:04:36.860 --> 00:04:38.028
My Lord...

00:04:39.613 --> 00:04:44.159
I permit it, you can fight
by way of entertainment.

00:04:44.410 --> 00:04:45.536
You are understanding.

00:04:47.621 --> 00:04:51.166
Even if this is for
entertainment, a duel is a duel.

00:04:51.542 --> 00:04:53.002
I'll give no quarter!

00:04:53.377 --> 00:04:54.670
Of course!

00:04:58.257 --> 00:04:59.383
Get ready!

00:04:59.925 --> 00:05:01.677
No need, come anytime.

00:05:02.303 --> 00:05:03.304
Nonsense...

00:05:03.637 --> 00:05:05.306
Won't you prepare yourself?

00:05:46.597 --> 00:05:48.599
I-I-I yield...

00:05:48.849 --> 00:05:49.475
Oh, my!

00:05:49.600 --> 00:05:51.226
That man did it!

00:06:00.319 --> 00:06:02.112
Well done, well clone.

00:06:03.989 --> 00:06:07.076
Why don't you think about serving me?

00:06:07.326 --> 00:06:08.994
Of course, I'll treat you to rich rewards.

00:06:09.453 --> 00:06:13.123
Thanks, but I'm not
interested in that sort of thing...

00:06:16.335 --> 00:06:18.003
My Lord...

00:06:18.128 --> 00:06:19.213
Too bad...

00:06:19.338 --> 00:06:21.882
To let a skilled man like him stay idle...

00:06:40.651 --> 00:06:41.652
Guts!

00:06:42.486 --> 00:06:43.362
Guts!

00:06:43.529 --> 00:06:44.780
Welcome back!

00:06:44.905 --> 00:06:45.739
Easy, easy.

00:06:45.864 --> 00:06:47.616
I was worried about you...

00:06:47.658 --> 00:06:50.160
...because you had
disappeared when I woke up, Guts.

00:06:52.287 --> 00:06:55.791
But grandpa Godo was right after all.

00:06:57.167 --> 00:06:59.795
He told me that you
would come back here, for sure!

00:07:07.010 --> 00:07:09.680
Sorry, but can you deal with this again?

00:07:10.806 --> 00:07:11.807
Oh, boy...

00:07:12.683 --> 00:07:15.185
After spending a week
sitting around doing nothing...

00:07:15.436 --> 00:07:17.646
...you suddenly try
your skill in a tournament.

00:07:19.690 --> 00:07:21.024
I see...

00:07:21.567 --> 00:07:25.070
<i>...you</i> fought against a
very skilled man this time...

00:07:26.321 --> 00:07:28.073
A sword doesn't lie.

00:07:28.699 --> 00:07:32.828
I can clearly see everything about both
you and your opponent from this sword.

00:07:34.037 --> 00:07:36.165
Oh, this poor sword of yours...

00:07:37.833 --> 00:07:41.670
It's wielded by a man
who is blind to his own destiny.

00:07:43.088 --> 00:07:46.717
Let me fix the sword, please?

00:07:47.050 --> 00:07:49.344
When you grow up, Erica.

00:08:11.492 --> 00:08:12.701
My destiny...

00:08:13.494 --> 00:08:14.870
My dream...

00:08:20.501 --> 00:08:23.629
Does this sword embody my dream?

00:08:24.213 --> 00:08:25.631
Guts!

00:08:26.006 --> 00:08:27.382
Here we go!

00:08:27.633 --> 00:08:28.509
Okay!

00:08:49.321 --> 00:08:50.405
Guts!

00:09:01.959 --> 00:09:05.712
It was impossible to deal
with so many at once, after all!

00:09:05.837 --> 00:09:07.089
Yeah, it was.

00:09:11.093 --> 00:09:12.719
This is reality.

00:09:13.220 --> 00:09:15.222
This has been by my side.

00:09:16.098 --> 00:09:18.809
Yes, this is a part of my body.

00:09:31.446 --> 00:09:33.574
Pain that I could hardly bear...

00:09:34.116 --> 00:09:36.243
Whenever I face the
moment of my death...

00:09:36.994 --> 00:09:39.121
...my sword is with
me as I move past it.

00:09:46.003 --> 00:09:47.337
Here's one!

00:09:51.258 --> 00:09:54.970
An unforgettable dream
and unforgettable people...

00:09:56.263 --> 00:10:00.225
I've felt everything
through the tip of my sword.

00:10:02.352 --> 00:10:05.897
This sword proves that I am alive.

00:10:12.779 --> 00:10:13.655
Guts!

00:10:14.114 --> 00:10:15.157
Guts!

00:10:17.534 --> 00:10:18.243
Ouch!

00:10:18.410 --> 00:10:20.662
Come on, stay still!

00:10:20.912 --> 00:10:23.165
You are quite reckless.

00:10:37.929 --> 00:10:41.558
Godo, why did you
become a sword smith?

00:10:42.768 --> 00:10:45.437
This trade has been
passed down through my family.

00:10:46.521 --> 00:10:48.440
Do you like it?

00:10:48.690 --> 00:10:49.941
I don't know.

00:10:50.067 --> 00:10:51.193
Don't you know?

00:10:51.693 --> 00:10:54.071
Erica likes it because it's fun.

00:10:54.321 --> 00:10:56.531
I want to be a sword smith, too!

00:10:56.657 --> 00:10:58.075
Hey, be careful.

00:11:00.410 --> 00:11:03.914
I've gripped steel
before I even learned to walk.

00:11:06.083 --> 00:11:07.334
I strike...

00:11:08.669 --> 00:11:10.712
...the iron lying before me...

00:11:11.713 --> 00:11:14.800
...without thinking
about whether I like it or not.

00:11:15.592 --> 00:11:19.971
I've been desperate to forge better
swords and to become a more skilled smith...

00:11:20.555 --> 00:11:23.225
...and I reached this age all too soon.

00:11:24.559 --> 00:11:29.356
If you ask why I keep hitting
the iron, I have no answer, but...

00:11:31.692 --> 00:11:35.737
There's one thing that I like about it.

00:11:37.864 --> 00:11:39.241
Sparks...

00:11:40.367 --> 00:11:41.993
I like seeing sparks...

00:11:42.994 --> 00:11:44.746
I'm absorbed by them.

00:11:44.871 --> 00:11:50.752
I can feel as if my life is sparking
before my eyes for a moment.

00:12:08.395 --> 00:12:09.521
Sparks...

00:12:10.522 --> 00:12:12.149
Am I also attracted...

00:12:12.649 --> 00:12:13.525
...to sparks?

00:12:14.985 --> 00:12:16.528
Light cascading off swords...

00:12:16.653 --> 00:12:17.904
They all cry sparks...

00:12:19.156 --> 00:12:21.283
All the times I have
lived through cry them...

00:12:22.284 --> 00:12:25.912
My own existence does too, and
the times and existences of others...

00:12:28.039 --> 00:12:31.042
That's what life is.

00:12:34.796 --> 00:12:37.007
Guts, ready?

00:12:37.257 --> 00:12:37.924
Yeah!

00:12:57.527 --> 00:12:58.820
You did it!

00:12:59.070 --> 00:13:00.447
Guts!

00:13:00.572 --> 00:13:02.324
Finally, you did it!

00:13:02.449 --> 00:13:05.660
After all, there's
nothing left but this for me.

00:13:08.455 --> 00:13:14.085
I wield my sword only for
myself, not for someone else.

00:13:15.045 --> 00:13:19.466
To give off sparks in a moment of life...

00:13:47.869 --> 00:13:49.120
Are you leaving?

00:13:49.246 --> 00:13:51.373
Yeah, thanks for your help.

00:13:51.498 --> 00:13:55.961
Huh, even though you lived off us for
nearly a year, your words are so simple.

00:13:56.878 --> 00:13:59.130
Take care of yourself.

00:13:59.464 --> 00:14:02.634
Of course I will, even
if you didn't tell me to.

00:14:04.886 --> 00:14:05.762
Bye now.

00:14:08.640 --> 00:14:09.266
Hey...

00:14:11.893 --> 00:14:13.645
Don't waste your life.

00:14:22.487 --> 00:14:24.531
Master Godo!

00:14:30.620 --> 00:14:36.042
What's the idea, coming over
here so early in the morning?

00:14:36.376 --> 00:14:39.671
Don't act like that, I came
here to make an order, as usual.

00:14:39.796 --> 00:14:40.755
An order?

00:14:41.006 --> 00:14:44.759
I want you to make as many
swords as you can, immediately.

00:14:45.010 --> 00:14:47.137
Of course I'll pay you, generously.

00:14:47.262 --> 00:14:48.054
What is it?

00:14:48.179 --> 00:14:49.556
A war started?

00:14:49.890 --> 00:14:51.182
Nope!

00:14:51.308 --> 00:14:52.559
Hunting bandits!

00:14:52.893 --> 00:14:54.185
Hunting bandits?

00:14:54.769 --> 00:14:56.646
A troop of bandits are on the run...

00:14:56.771 --> 00:14:59.316
...hiding in the
mountains just over the border.

00:14:59.441 --> 00:15:02.777
I need weapons so I can make
some easy money before it's too late.

00:15:03.069 --> 00:15:04.529
Bandits on the run?

00:15:04.654 --> 00:15:06.531
You hadn't heard?

00:15:06.698 --> 00:15:07.824
You neither, Master?

00:15:08.533 --> 00:15:09.826
Naturally.

00:15:09.951 --> 00:15:12.829
You live like a hermit down here.

00:15:13.204 --> 00:15:16.541
Who are they, these bandits on the run?

00:15:17.042 --> 00:15:20.170
They used to be a mercenary
band that staged some kind of revolt...

00:15:20.295 --> 00:15:21.963
...in Windam about a year ago.

00:15:22.422 --> 00:15:23.590
A mercenary band?

00:15:23.798 --> 00:15:27.969
Yes, I'm told that they are led
by a woman with incredible skills.

00:15:28.803 --> 00:15:29.679
A woman?

00:15:30.096 --> 00:15:34.726
I heard that they also made a
really big impact in the hundred-year war.

00:15:35.101 --> 00:15:38.355
I don't remember the name, though...

00:15:38.730 --> 00:15:41.983
...probably the Band
of something, Band of...

00:15:42.108 --> 00:15:42.567
Yes!

00:15:42.692 --> 00:15:43.693
The Band of the Hawk!

00:15:44.945 --> 00:15:46.738
Wait, what did you just say?

00:15:46.821 --> 00:15:47.614
Huh?

00:15:47.739 --> 00:15:49.324
I'm asking you what you said!

00:15:49.741 --> 00:15:50.617
W-Well...

00:15:50.742 --> 00:15:54.371
I said the Band of the Hawk
led by a woman named Caska.

00:16:11.513 --> 00:16:13.515
We finally found them...

00:16:13.598 --> 00:16:14.641
...the Band of the Hawk.

00:16:14.849 --> 00:16:17.602
Damn, they gave us a lot of trouble.

00:16:18.144 --> 00:16:22.649
Don't complain about it,
they will meet their end tonight.

00:16:23.274 --> 00:16:25.777
I'll make sure they sleep forever.

00:17:01.688 --> 00:17:04.941
Don't work too hard,
or you'll fall right over.

00:17:05.734 --> 00:17:06.609
Judeau...

00:17:07.277 --> 00:17:09.112
I understand your feelings.

00:17:09.904 --> 00:17:13.491
But you are virtually
the Hawks' only leader now.

00:17:14.993 --> 00:17:17.787
Everyone is tired because
we've been living on the run.

00:17:18.163 --> 00:17:20.665
What if you collapsed
at this crucial moment?

00:17:20.790 --> 00:17:21.750
I know.

00:17:22.542 --> 00:17:25.295
A moment ago, I got a
report from our comrades...

00:17:25.420 --> 00:17:26.546
...who infiltrated Windam.

00:17:27.297 --> 00:17:30.800
According to their report, Griffith is
imprisoned in an underground dungeon...

00:17:30.925 --> 00:17:33.678
...that is located on the
lowest level of Windam palace.

00:17:34.804 --> 00:17:39.017
Some of them have heard a
voice rising up from the prison...

00:17:39.809 --> 00:17:42.062
...it could be him
screaming or moaning.

00:17:43.063 --> 00:17:44.064
However...

00:17:44.898 --> 00:17:47.901
...the voice has not
been heard within this month.

00:17:51.071 --> 00:17:52.572
Everyone is exhausted.

00:17:53.073 --> 00:17:56.201
How can we plan his escape
when we are already at our limits?

00:17:57.160 --> 00:17:58.078
Believe in them.

00:17:59.079 --> 00:18:01.081
You've got to believe in your comrades.

00:18:01.706 --> 00:18:05.210
We have no choice but to
pool our talents, every one of us.

00:18:05.710 --> 00:18:06.586
Judeau...

00:18:07.545 --> 00:18:09.714
Anyhow, you should
at least get some rest.

00:18:09.839 --> 00:18:13.593
You can't organize our mission
to rescue Griffith if you are so tired...

00:18:14.969 --> 00:18:16.346
You are right...

00:18:16.596 --> 00:18:18.223
You need to eat and rest.

00:18:18.973 --> 00:18:19.808
Yeah...

00:18:24.229 --> 00:18:24.854
Judeau...

00:18:27.607 --> 00:18:28.441
Thank you.

00:19:01.391 --> 00:19:02.767
How's Caska?

00:19:03.143 --> 00:19:04.853
Taking a little rest.

00:19:05.145 --> 00:19:06.521
She should.

00:19:06.855 --> 00:19:09.107
Lately, she hasn't slept at all.

00:19:09.732 --> 00:19:12.110
Actually, she is taking things very well.

00:19:12.402 --> 00:19:15.989
If she didn't take up the
position of leader, we would have...

00:19:16.239 --> 00:19:19.742
I know, we could never
have survived until now...

00:19:21.286 --> 00:19:23.663
We have survived, and so what?

00:19:25.039 --> 00:19:30.170
It's totally impossible to make
a fresh start, even if we survive...

00:19:30.295 --> 00:19:32.297
...and make it to another country.

00:19:33.631 --> 00:19:38.011
In the first place, the Hawks
are just a rabble without Griffith.

00:19:38.178 --> 00:19:40.013
We can accomplish nothing.

00:19:40.138 --> 00:19:41.514
What are you talking about?

00:19:41.556 --> 00:19:44.517
Of course we need him, that's
why we are all trying to rescue him!

00:19:45.685 --> 00:19:48.438
Can you prove that Griffith is still alive?

00:19:51.524 --> 00:19:54.569
I wonder if it's all over...

00:19:55.195 --> 00:19:56.821
Everything has been...

00:19:57.447 --> 00:19:59.699
Then why are you here, Corkus?

00:19:59.824 --> 00:20:02.660
Why didn't you
leave with the deserters?

00:20:09.959 --> 00:20:11.211
Ricket...

00:20:12.212 --> 00:20:15.173
I wish he was here for us...

00:20:23.431 --> 00:20:24.349
What is it?

00:20:32.607 --> 00:20:33.441
Enemy raid!

00:20:40.240 --> 00:20:41.699
The enemy is in the north woods!

00:20:41.866 --> 00:20:43.868
Third Company, Fourth
Company, counterattack!

00:20:44.118 --> 00:20:47.747
Everyone else, carry the injured to the
carriages and ride to the southern quarter!

00:21:08.226 --> 00:21:08.977
Caska!

00:21:10.395 --> 00:21:11.521
I have you!

00:21:27.287 --> 00:21:29.539
Stay alert, Captain.

00:21:37.130 --> 00:21:38.047
Guts...

00:22:02.947 --> 00:22:05.033
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:08.703
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:09.954 --> 00:22:12.707
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:12.832 --> 00:22:15.710
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.420 --> 00:22:18.963
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:19.088 --> 00:22:20.214
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.340 --> 00:22:23.426
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.719 --> 00:22:27.597
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.680 --> 00:22:30.933
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:31.225 --> 00:22:34.562
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:34.979 --> 00:22:37.940
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.608 --> 00:22:41.611
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.487 --> 00:22:45.323
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.888
Next Episode

00:23:09.639 --> 00:23:14.519
Unless one loses a precious thing,
he will never know its true value.

00:23:15.144 --> 00:23:20.274
A light scratches the darkness, and the
exhausted one faces his shattered dream...

00:23:20.608 --> 00:23:23.111
...realizing his path cannot be walked.

00:23:23.778 --> 00:23:31.160
Is there any way a man can live happily
without embracing his wounded heart?

00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:36.916
Confession

00:23:37.305 --> 00:24:37.292
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

